				\begin{document}$${M}_{y}$$\end{document}My the meridional mass transport. Negative wind stress curl anomalies enhance the subtropical anticyclonic circulation while weakening the cyclonic subarctic gyre. Although the Sverdrup relation represents the steady-state solution, our analysis does not concentrate on the transition of ocean circulation between its positive and negative phases (Fig. 2a, d), which pertains to time-varying solutions. Rather, the Sverdrup relation here explains the ocean circulation during these two phases.

Given the Sverdrup relation (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
